##Huang Qifan: The proposed abolition of Housing Provident Fund, for enterprises and workers to reduce costs by 12%

Reporter: Xin Yuan

“

In the face of the new pneumonia epidemic, Huang Qifan said that in addition to the tax and other policies currently adopted by governments at all levels, it is proposed to speed up reform in four areas, including the implementation of migrant workers in the city as soon as possible, the abolition of the Enterprise Housing Provident Fund system, the introduction of policies to encourage enterprises to implement the annuity system, trying to reduce logistics costs.

”

“

In the face of the new pneumonia epidemic, Huang Qifan said that in addition to the tax and other policies currently adopted by governments at all levels, it is proposed to speed up reform in four areas, including the implementation of migrant workers in the city as soon as possible, the abolition of the Enterprise Housing Provident Fund system, the introduction of policies to encourage enterprises to implement the annuity system, trying to reduce logistics costs.

”

COVID-19 adds to the uncertainty in the Chinese economy, despite recent moves by central and local governments to reduce the impact of the epidemic on businesses, from taxes to financing, but Huang Qifan, a former vice chairman of the NPC's financial and Economic Affairs Committee and Chairman of the Tsinghua Industry Transformation Advisory Committee, said the measures were far from sufficient and suggested four areas for urgent reform.

As Huang Qifan pointed out in an article titled "Several Suggestions for Economic Development and manufacturing resumption under the new crown epidemic" published on Wechat Public Account "Tsinghua University Internet Industry Research Institute" , the resumption of work and production will be resumed on February 10, it is stipulated in most regions, but it is still difficult for enterprises to resume work and production in a real sense.

First of all, he said, the control of the epidemic has led to an acute shortage of workers. There are many procedures for workers to return to the factory, and the concerns of governments at all levels can indeed be understood. It is really a helpless act that every detail is important, such as the approval of applications for returning to work, training for returning to work, prevention and control of the epidemic, and management and control of personnel. However, as long as the formalities are complete, the efficiency is still very fast. But workers still can not come back, road closure, village closure, persuade back, refused entry, household registration, housing, isolation time and other issues, which is the first major difficulty leading to the resumption of work.

Second, the epidemic has crippled supply chains in many industries. Most companies around the country have a lot of external cooperation parts suppliers, everyone will face a shortage of workers, materials, parts shortage. These enterprises are located in different areas of different cities, different policies and procedures, different production time to restore, matching each other extremely difficult, which is the second most difficult point.

Third, the epidemic period of enterprise logistics transport almost to a standstill. In addition to the epidemic necessary materials, all over the country set up various checkpoints, suppliers of raw materials, spare parts can not come in, after the resumption of production products can not be shipped out. At the same time, the restrictions on the movement of people make it very difficult to develop the market, especially in foreign trade. At present, more than 60 countries restrict China's entry and the market losses are huge.

In Huang Qifan's view, to solve these three problems, in addition to the current tax policy at all levels of government, proposed to speed up the four areas of reform.

First, we will implement the policy of settling migrant workers in cities as soon as possible and solve the problem of labor shortage in the manufacturing industry. If 200 million of the 300 million migrant workers can settle down in cities, it will not only relieve the pressure of the Spring Festival travel rush, but also quickly replenish the urban labor force, effectively extend the working age of migrant workers, the annual working hours and the opportunity period of the demographic dividend.

Second, the abolition of Enterprise Housing Accumulation Fund system. The Housing Provident Fund system was first learned from Singapore in 1990s, and now our country's real estate has long been commercialized, commercial banks have become the main providers of housing loans, and the significance of the existence of housing provident fund is already not great, eliminating it would cut costs for businesses and workers by 12 percent.

Third, the introduction of policies to encourage enterprises to implement the annuity system, and dredge the investment capital market channels and mechanisms of enterprise annuity. This is not only beneficial to supplement the social pension funds, but also conducive to the formation of a huge long-term capital supply for the prosperity and stability of the capital market.

Fourth, try every means to reduce logistics costs. The outbreak will bring significant opportunities to some "online" industries, but also put forward higher requirements for logistics efficiency. It is suggested that the proportion of railway freight volume should be increased, the railway line should be extended to various development zones, factories and mining enterprises as soon as possible, the "last kilometer" of railway transportation should be opened up, and the cost of comprehensive logistics should be reduced.
